In summary, the results in this work are fourfold: •an explicit basis of irreducible eMZVs of certain weights and lengths, together with expres- sions of eMZVs in that basis collected on a web page https://tools.aei.mpg.de/emzv •the observation that Fay, shuﬄe and reﬂection relations generate all identities between eMZVs up to the weights and lengths considered.

•several explicit new relations in the special derivation algebra u, which are collected also athttps://tools.aei.mpg.de/emzv The article is organized as follows: section 2 starts with a small review of eMZVs and sets the stage for combining Fay and shuﬄe relations with the q-expansion, resulting in an “observa- tional” set of indecomposable eMZVs.
A table containing the elements missing here is available at https://tools.aei.mpg.de/emzv .

Basis rules for rewriting each eMZV in terms of those indecomposable elements can be obtained in digital form from the web page https://tools.aei.mpg.de/emzv and are available up to and including weights 30 ,18,12,10 for lengths 3 ,4,5,6, respectively.

Irreducible relations at higher depth can be obtained in electronic form from the website https://tools.aei.mpg.de/emzv , whereas relations of depth three at w= 16,20 and depth four atw= 18,22 are provided in ref.
(C.5) The complete set of all irreducible relations known to us is available from https://tools.aei.mpg.de/emzv , and all of them have been veriﬁed by evaluating the action on the letters x,yvia eq.
